textBeforeTable: Meeting agendas are posted at each school site. Discussion is limited to school business. Confidential matters regarding individual students and personnel will not be discussed during public meetings. School board meetings may vary slightly, but each will allow public comment and time to address an agenda item. You may do so by signing in at the beginning of the meeting, or by raising your hand to be recognized. It´s always a good idea to call and verify that a meeting has not been cancelled or changed. The role of each local district board is to establish a vision for the district, set policies for how the district is run, oversee district operations, and hire the district superintendent. School District Boards Agendas are posted at Trinidad Town Hall, the post office and Murphy´s Market. Anyone wishing to place an item on the agenda should call 677-0223 at least one week before the meeting. Citizens are allowed to address a non-agenda or agenda item during the public comment time of the meeting, either by signing in or raising their hand and standing to be recognized. May meet on 4th Wednesdays also, if necessary. 2nd Wednesdays, 7 P.M. Meets: 677-0223 409 Trinity St., Trinidad 95570 Trinidad City Council Vacant Jack West Dwight Miller Jim Baker
